4. Reading and Writing Files
Question1 : Reading from a file using read(), readline(), readlines().
ANswer  :
1. read() – Read Entire File : Reads the whole file content as a single string
2. readline() – Read One Line at a Time : Reads one line per call
3. readlines() – Read All Lines as List : Reads all lines and stores them in a list

Question2 :Writing to a file using write() and writelines().
Answer :
1. write() – Write a Single String : Writes one string at a time to the file
Does not automatically add a newline (\n)
2. writelines() – Write Multiple Strings : Writes a list of strings to the file
Does not add newline automatically, so include \n manually
