5. Exception Handling
Question 1 : Introduction to exceptions and how to handle them using try, except, and finally
ANswer :An exception is an error that occurs during the execution of a program (runtime error).
When an exception occurs, the program crashes unless it is handled properly.
| Keyword   | Purpose                   |
| --------- | ------------------------- |
| `try`     | Code that may cause error |
| `except`  | Handles the error         |
| `finally` | Always executes           |

