7. Inheritance
Question 1 : Single, Multilevel, Multiple, Hierarchical, and Hybrid inheritance in Python.
Answer  :
1.Single Inheritance : One child class inherits from one parent class
2.Multilevel Inheritance : A class inherits from a class, which itself inherits from another class
3. Multiple Inheritance : One child class inherits from more than one parent class
4. Hierarchical Inheritance  :Multiple child classes inherit from one parent class
5. Hybrid Inheritance : Combination of two or more types of inheritance

Question 2 :Using the super() function to access properties of the parent class.
ANswer : The super() function is used to access methods and properties of the parent (base) class
from the child class. It helps in reusing code and is especially useful in inheritance.
Why use super()?
Avoid writing parent class name explicitly
Supports code reusability
Works well with multiple inheritance (MRO)
Helps call parent constructor (__init__)

