10. Search and Match Functions

Question1 : Using re.search() and re.match() functions in Python’s re module for pattern
matching
Answer :
1. re.match(). :Checks for a match only at the beginning of the string
2. re.search() : Searches for a pattern anywhere in the string

Question 2. :Difference between search and match.
| Feature      | `re.match()`             | `re.search()`          |
| ------------ | ------------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Position     | Start of string only     | Anywhere in string     |
| Flexibility  | Less flexible            | More flexible          |
| Use Case     | Check prefix (beginning) | Find pattern anywhere  |
| Return Value | Match object or `None`   | Match object or `None` |









